<subSubSection id="49C942EEFF9D3945EBD2C5B4FDED58BA" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="016C1165FF9D3945EBD2C5B4FEAA5997" blockId="51.[227,341,647,673]" box="[227,341,647,673]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<heading id="5A24A609FF9D3945EBD2C5B4FEAA5997" bold="true" box="[227,341,647,673]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF9D3945EBD2C5B4FEAA5997" bold="true" box="[227,341,647,673]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FF9D3945EBD2C584FDED58BA" blockId="51.[226,1437,695,908]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Otoliths of this species are only known by specimens from the Yazoo Clay (Priabonian) of Louisiana. They are closely related to those of the species originally described as 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF9D3945EF2CC5EEFE9E582A" authority="Stinton &amp; Nolf, 1970" authorityName="Stinton &amp; Nolf" authorityYear="1970" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Lepophidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aequalis">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF9D3945EF2CC5EEFADD59C1" box="[1053,1314,733,759]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Lepophidium aequalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FF9D3945EE18C5EEFE9E582A" author="Stinton &amp; Nolf" firstAuthor="Stinton" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="219 - 234" refId="ref57622" refString="Stinton F. C. &amp; Nolf D. 1970. A teleost otolith fauna from the Sands of Lede, Belgium. Bulletin de la Societe belge de Geologie, de Paleontologie et d'Hydrologie 78: 219 - 234." type="journal article" year="1970">Stinton &amp; Nolf, 1970</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the Belgian Lede Formation (Lutetian), that 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FF9D3945E89DC431FB54582B" author="Schwarzhans" box="[940,1195,770,797]" firstAuthor="Schwarzhans" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="63 - 122" refId="ref56686" refString="Schwarzhans W. 1981 b. Vergleichende morphologische Untersuchungen an rezenten und fossilen Otolithen der Ordnung Ophidiiformes. Berliner geowissenschaftliche Abhandlungen A 32: 63 - 122." type="journal article" year="1981" yearSuffix="b">Schwarzhans (1981b)</bibRefCitation>
placed in the extinct genus 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF9D3945EA02C414FE0F5877" authorityName="Schwarzhans" authorityYear="1981" box="[307,496,807,833]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Aequalobythites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF9D3945EA02C414FE0F5877" box="[307,496,807,833]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Aequalobythites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Other related species are 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF9D3945E871C41BFB7D5877" authority="(Priem, 1911)" baseAuthorityName="Priem" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[832,1154,807,834]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Aequalobythites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="regularis">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF9D3945E871C41BFC305877" box="[832,975,807,834]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">A. regularis</emphasis>
(Priem, 1911)
</taxonomicName>
from the Lutetian and Bartonian of the Paris Basin, 
<collectingCountry id="79C451F5FF9D3945E909C47FFD625850" box="[568,669,844,870]" name="Belgium" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Belgium</collectingCountry>
and southern 
<collectingCountry id="79C451F5FF9D3945E871C47FFC5A5850" box="[832,933,844,870]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">England</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF9D3945E8D1C47EFACC5851" authority="(Koken, 1891)" baseAuthorityName="Koken" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[992,1331,844,871]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Aequalobythites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hilgendorfi">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF9D3945E8D1C47EFB7E5850" box="[992,1153,844,871]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">A. hilgendorfi</emphasis>
(Koken, 1891)
</taxonomicName>
from the German lower Oligocene.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
